  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add the<strong> bacon</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1.-jpg-copy-2-1610471846909-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1.-jpg-copy-2-1610471846909-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1.-jpg-copy-2-1610471846909-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1.-jpg-copy-2-1610471846909-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1.-jpg-copy-2-1610471846909-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the bacon is in the oven, chop the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to a separate baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-12 min or until lightly charred and caramelised</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1610471786526-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1610471786526-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1610471786526-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1610471786526-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1610471786526-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the tomatoes are in the oven, top, tail then grate the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onions </strong>finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1610471858833-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1610471858833-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1610471858833-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1610471858833-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1610471858833-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated courgette</strong> to the middle of a clean tea towel (or kitchen paper) and bring the four corners together to form a ball, twist the ball and squeeze out as much of the liquid as you can</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1610471865846-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1610471865846-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1610471865846-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1610471865846-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1610471865846-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>grated courgette </strong>to a bowl with most of the <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>(save a little for garnish!), the <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, <strong>cornflour</strong>, 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2] </span><strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> fritter mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1610471876772-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1610471876772-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1610471876772-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1610471876772-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1610471876772-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, spoon the <strong>fritter mixture</strong> into the pan, roughly divided into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8] </span>and cook for 3 min on each side or until golden and cooked through (save the pan for the next step!) – these are your <strong>cheesy courgette fritters</strong></p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1610471883875-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1610471883875-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1610471883875-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1610471883875-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1610471883875-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>courgette fritters</strong> to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and put them in the oven to keep warm</p><p>Return the fritter pan to a medium-low heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, crack the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>eggs</strong> into the pan</p><p>Tip: Give your eggs a little shake before you crack for perfectly centred yolks!</p><p>Cover with a lid and cook for 2-3 min or until done to your liking</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1610471894360-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1610471894360-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1610471894360-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1610471894360-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1610471894360-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer the <strong>cheesy courgette fritters</strong> on top of one another</p><p>Top the fritters with a <strong>fried egg</strong> and serve the <strong>crispy bacon</strong> and <strong>roasted cherry tomatoes</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the <strong>remaining sliced spring onion </strong>and a grind of<strong> pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
